The new user is working end-to-end: Partner Repository finds `gps000001`, Arthur creates the session, and B2Boost successfully exchanges the handoff.

The missing values are visible in the Stub Server log:

```text
email=null
firstName=null
lastName=null
brandContext=null
```

But Partner Repository is returning those values correctly. Its log shows:

```text
userInfo=UserInfoResponse(
  firstName=John,
  lastName=Doe,
  phoneNumbers=[...],
  emails=[john.doe@orange.example.com]
)
```

So the issue is in **Arthur Core mapping Partner Repository `UserResponse` into `UserSession`**.

## What is happening

Your Partner Repository response structure is likely:

```java
UserResponse
    userId
    username
    userInfo
        firstName
        lastName
        emails
        phoneNumbers
    salesPoints
    roles
```

But Arthur is probably doing only:

```java
session.setUserId(userResponse.getUserId());
session.setUsername(userResponse.getUsername());
session.setRoles(userResponse.getRoles());
session.setSalesPoints(userResponse.getSalesPoints());
```

It needs to map the nested `userInfo`.

## Update `AuthService.handleCallback(...)`

Where you create `UserSession`, add:

```java
UserInfoResponse userInfo = userResponse.getUserInfo();

session.setUserId(userResponse.getUserId());
session.setUsername(userResponse.getUsername());
session.setRoles(userResponse.getRoles());
session.setSalesPoints(userResponse.getSalesPoints());

if (userInfo != null) {
    session.setFirstName(userInfo.getFirstName());
    session.setLastName(userInfo.getLastName());

    if (userInfo.getEmails() != null && !userInfo.getEmails().isEmpty()) {
        session.setEmail(userInfo.getEmails().getFirst());
    }

    if (userInfo.getPhoneNumbers() != null
            && !userInfo.getPhoneNumbers().isEmpty()) {
        session.setPhoneNumber(userInfo.getPhoneNumbers().getFirst());
    }
}
```

Use `get(0)` instead of `getFirst()` if your Java version does not support `List.getFirst()`:

```java
session.setEmail(userInfo.getEmails().get(0));
session.setPhoneNumber(userInfo.getPhoneNumbers().get(0));
```

